      <h2>Summary: Your Shop Vac Maintenance Routine</h2>
      <div style="background:#1a2332;border:1px solid #2a3a4e;border-radius:0.5rem;padding:1.25rem;margin:1.5rem 0">
        <p><strong>🔹 After each shift (2 min):</strong> Empty tank → Tap/brush filter → Check hose for blockages → Coil hose → Store dry</p>
        <p><strong>🔹 Every Friday (10 min):</strong> Wash cartridge filter → Rinse foam sleeve (if used) → Inspect attachments → Wipe tank interior → Check cord</p>
        <p><strong>🔹 Every month (20–30 min):</strong> Deep clean filter → Sanitize tank → Inspect seals → Clean exhaust/muffler → Lubricate wheels</p>
        <p><strong>🔹 Every 6 months:</strong> Replace filter if worn → Check gasket for cracks → Test float valve → Replace foam muffler if degraded</p>
      </div>
      <p>Follow this routine and your shop vac will deliver full suction for years — saving you hundreds in replacement costs and keeping your job site cleaner, shift after shift.</p>

